Learn and Experience
K Camps focus on building environment consciousness, social
responsibility, self-confidence, leadership skills, critical thinking
and creativity.
In his experiential learning theory, Kolb described two different
ways of grasping experience:
Concrete Experience & Abstract Conceptualisation
He also identified two ways of transforming experience:
Reflective Observation & Active or reflective experimentation
All our camps are based on themes to provide practical tools & guides to create real time impact
in the children’s lives. We focus on creating experiences to make the learning profound and long-
lasting. With emphasis on hands-on work, we encourage creativity and leadership skills to
emerge naturally based on the children’s inclination. Camps are open to children and youth
between the ages of 10 and 21.
Children explore practical ways to make a difference to the
environment & create practices that cause positive impact to
the community you live in and learn cool things to contribute
your bit to a more environment friendly world by making
conscious and responsible choices
Location
These are non-residential camps held in Mangalore & Bangalore .

Self-Exploration Camps
Who is it for?
Our camps are open for children from all social backgrounds. With an intake of only 20 children
per camp, we focus on delivering value and creating mindsets in the chosen theme. 30% of the
children come from socially backward backgrounds. We believe that all children irrespective of
their social background deserve the right to experiential learning. While only a fraction of our
privileged society get access to such learning opportunities, it is equally important to enable the
rest of the society with the same opportunities because they make up the bulk of the society
Contribution
By sending children to our camps, the contribution enables us to provide the same opportunity
to those who cannot afford. Parents investment therefore is not only in their child but in the
community as a whole. All proceeds go towards managing operations for the camps and funding
30% of the children attending our camps who are on full scholarship.
These children get equal opportunities alongside privileged children, thereby creating a more
conscious and responsible community for these future global citizens.
